    %h5 The Approach
    %p
      Within this program we would focus on a number of ideas that we want to explore with The Puzzle School:
    %ul.no_shift.spaced_out
      %li
        Exposing students to a variety of challenges and interesting problems that can stimulate
        their creative problem-solving abilities.
      %li
        Having students test resources and provide feedback
        in order to find the best resources students can use to learn at their own pace.
      %li
        Having students engage in a variety of design exercises to help foster ideas, techniques, and skills
        such as rapid-prototyping and team communication.
      %li
        Running retrospectives at the end of each sessions to get feedback from students around
        what worked and didn't with regard to the challenge, their work and solution, and the overall
        environment they are working in.
      %li
        Supporting students toward independent and small group projects (inventions) they design
        themselves and will continue working on at home.

    %p
      Some of the resources and activities we've had success with include:
    %ul.no_shift.spaced_out
      %li= link_to('CodeCombat', 'https://codecombat.com/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Project Euler', 'https://projecteuler.net/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Drawing In Code', 'https://jaredcosulich.github.io/drawing_code', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Marshmallow Towers', 'http://www.tomwujec.com/design-projects/marshmallow-challenge/', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Popsicle Stick Bridges', 'http://courses.washington.edu/engr100/Section_Brad/01_hnd_BridgeIntro.htm', target: '_blank')
      %li= link_to('Rubber Band Catapults', 'http://kidsactivitiesblog.com/55055/15-easy-catapults-to-make', target: '_blank')

